T1  - Reswitching, primary inputs and the Heckscher-Ohlin-Samuelson theory of trade
AU  - Steedman, Ian
AU  - Metcalfe, J.S.
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 7
IS  - 2
SP  - 201
EP  - 208
PY  - 1977
DA  - 1977/05/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(77)90031-9
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199677900319
AB  - The 2× 2 × 2 Heckscher-Ohlin-Samuelson model of trade is examined under all the usual assumptions, except that a positive rate of interest is assumed. The factor-price-equalization and Stolper-Samuelson theorems are shown to be unaffected by the positive interest rate. The H-O-S theorem on the pattern of trade still holds in its ‘quantity’ form but is shown to be invalid in its ‘price’ form. Consequently trade need not ‘harm’ a country's scarce factor. It is to be expected that, in general, international equilibrium will not be unique.
ER  - 
